f%20a%20cut%20in%20September%20after%20the%20new%20inflation%20report%2C%20up%20from%20the%20roughly%2080%25%20likelihood%20before%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20core%20annual%20inflation%20is%20back%20to%20its%20highest%20level%20since%20February%2C%20today's%20CPI%20print%20is%20not%20hot%20enough%20to%20derail%20the%20Fed%20from%20cutting%20rates%20in%20September%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Seema%20Shah%2C%20the%20chief%20global%20strategist%20at%20Principal%20Asset%20Management.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20some%20sign%20of%20tariff%20pass%20through%20to%20consumer%20prices%20but%2C%20at%20this%20stage%2C%20it%20is%20not%20significant%20enough%20to%20ring%20alarm%20bells.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20haven't%20taken%20the%20brunt%20of%20tariffs'%20impacts%2C%20at%20least%20not%20yet.%20A%20Goldman%20Sachs%20report%20on%20Sunday%20said%20US%20consumers%20have%20absorbed%20less%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20tariff%20costs%20through%20June%20but%20think%20it%20will%20jump%20to%2067%25%20by%20October%2C%20assuming%20newer%20tariffs%20have%20a%20similar%20impact%20to%20previous%20ones.%20Businesses%20and%20foreign%20exporters%20account%20for%20the%20remaining%20incidence%20of%20the%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiane%20Swonk%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20KPMG%20US%2C%20told%20PBS%20News%20Hour%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20tariffs%20are%20so%20large%20that%20they%20also%20squeeze%20profit%20margins%20and%20that%20means%20cost-cutting%20or%20layoffs.%26quot%3B%20So%20far%2C%20US%20layoffs%20have%20remained%20at%20their%20low%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20worried%20about%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstagflation-us-economy-outlook-tariffs-inflation-job-market-hiring-slowdown-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esort%20of%20stagflationary%3C%2Fa%3E%20kind%20of%20nature%20of%20these%20tariffs%20because%20they're%20so%20large%20and%20they're%20just%20unable%20to%20be%20completely%20absorbed%20by%20ei