crosoft-amazon-aws-azure-compare-cloud-giants-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EMicrosoft%20Azure%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20She's%20worked%20at%20the%20company%20since%202019.%20Her%20employment%20and%20promotions%C2%A0were%20confirmed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20I%20learned%20the%20strategy%20of%20getting%20promotions%20the%20hard%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-pay-guidelines-new-hire-offers-exception-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejoined%20Microsoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20April%202019%20as%20a%20new%20college%20grad%2C%20I%20guess%20I%20was%20pretty%20nice.%20I%20did%20not%20know%20that%20I%20should%20be%20proactive%20about%20communicating%20my%20career%20aspirations%20with%20my%20manager.%20I%20just%20thought%20that%20if%20I%20consistently%20delivered%20good%20quality%20work%2C%20it%20would%20eventually%20naturally%20lead%20to%20promotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20a%20passive%20approach%2C%20and%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20disconnect%20where%20your%20manager%20or%20the%20leadership%20thinks%20that%20you%20are%20not%20necessarily%20career%20ambitious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20something%20I%20kind%20of%20missed%20during%20my%20first%20year.%20Since%20then%2C%20I%20have%20gotten%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-employee-one-on-one-meeting-strategy-for-promotions-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efour%20promotions%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20frequently%20request%20feedback%20from%20my%20manager%20and%20not%20necessarily%20wait%20for%20the%20review%20cycle.%20At%20Microsoft%2C%20our%20reviews%20are%20semiannual%2C%20but%20that%20means%20it%20could%20still%20take%20six%20months%20to%20find%20out%20that%20you%20haven't%20necessarily%20reached%20expectations%20for%20certain%20things.%20And%20you%20don't%20have%20enough%20time%20left%20to%20course%20correct%20at%20that%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20I%20generally%20do%20is%20have%20biweekly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pitch-change-in-role-to-your-manager-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eone-on-ones%20with%20my%20manager%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20try%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20once%20a%20month%20I%20bring%20up%20this%20topic%20and%20ask%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20think%20is%20going%20good%3F%20Do%20you%20think%20I%20could%20do%20something%20better%3F%20Is%20there%20anything%20that%20I%20might%20be%20overlooking%20and%20would%20you%20suggest%20I%20improve%20on%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20just%20for%20myself%2C%20I%20normally%20try%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-year-network-career-hobby-resolutions-goals-skills-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eset%20career%20goals%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20instance%2C%20I%20set%20a%20goal%20of%20reaching%20the%20next%20level%20within%2018%20to%2024%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2212293c14-9be6-4c3b-b8ee-7ec1c81e1f1d%5C%22%3EKnow%20what's%20expected%20of%20the%20level%20you%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20to%2C%20and%20be%20proactive%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20you%20need%20to%20understand%20is%20your%20expectations%3A%20what%20your%20manager%2C%20the%20team%2C%20and%20the%20company%20expect%20of%20a%20person%20at%20your%20current%20level%20and%20what%20they%20expect%20of%20a%20person%20at%20the%20next%20level.%20Then%2C%20you%20need%20to%20ask%20what%20the%20gap%20is%20between%20the%20two%20and%20how%20you%20can%20close%20that%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20self-awareness%2C%20or%20trying%20to%20be%20aware%20that%20this%20is%20what%20is%20expected%20of%20me.%20Am%20I%20hitting%20all%20of%20these%20checklist%20items%3F%20Am%20I%20missing%20something%3F%20Is%20there%20something%20that%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20I%20should%20know%3F%20Talking%20to%20peers%2C%20having%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-founder-ai-vision-meta-tips-product-market-fit-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20mentors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20talking%20to%20your%20manager%20can%20help%20you%20progress%20in%20this%20area%20when%20you%20try%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20you're%20lacking%20and%20what%C2%A0you%20need%20to%20do%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Microsoft%2C%20there%20is%20an%20internal%20website%20called%20the%20role%20library%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20descriptive.%20It%20says%20that%20if%20you're%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20X%2C%20Y%2C%20or%20Z%20level%2C%20this%20is%20what%20the%20company%20basically%20expects%20you%20to%20be%20performing%2C%20and%20all%20the%20tasks%20that%20you%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20doing%20on%20a%20day-to%E2%80%91day%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20company%20has%20something%20like%20that%2C%20check%20it.%20And%20then%20I%20would%20correlate%20that%20during%20the%20talks%20with%20my%20manager%20to%20see%20what%20I%20could%20be%20doing%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20knew%20that%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20get%20promoted%20to%20a%20senior%20level%2C%20it%20was%20expected%20that%20I%20deliver%20a%20project%20end-to-end.%20From%20the%20design%20phase%20to%20implementing%20and%20monitoring%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20you're%20rolling%20out%20with%20limited%20bugs.%20That%20was%20something%20I%20identified%20I%20needed%20and%20would%20have%20frequent%20conversations%20with%20my%20manager%C2%A0to%20put%20it%20out%20there%20to%20him.%20I'd%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20targeting%20my%20next%20promotion%2C%20I%20believe%20this%20is%20what%20I%20need%20to%20do.%20So%20how%20can%20we%20identify%20opportunities%20for%20such%20projects%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20gave%20my%20manager%20the%20impression%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20she%20looks%20to%20be%20ready%20and%20she's%20interested%20in%20doing%20more%20and%20delivering%20more%20than%20what%20she's%20actually%20doing%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20way%2C%20whenever%20there%20was%20a%20new%20feature%20or%20opportunity%2C%20my%20manager%20would%20remember%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20I%20have%20this%20one%20person%20who%20mentioned%20that%20she%20would%20be%20interested%20in%20picking%20up%20something%20like%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20promoted%20is%20not%20just%20doing%20the%20work%20that%20you've%20been%20asked%20to%20do%3B%20it's%20also%20taking%20ownership%2C%20taking%20control%2C%20and%20trying%20to%20find%20these%20opportunities%20for%20yourself.%20It's%20also%20not%20just%20about%20what%20work%20you%20are%20doing%3B%20sometimes%2C%20it%20also%20matters%20how%20high%20the%20impact%20of%20that%20work%20is%2C%20and%20it%20has%20to%20align%20with%20your%20team's%20goals%20and%20the%20company's%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20that%20got%20you%20the%20job%20or%20how%20you%20landed%20your%20big%20promotion%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-senior-software-engineer-strategy-promotions-career-track-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754998982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68967034194a2d49b8ae4dae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-senior-software-engineer-strategy-promotions-career-track-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ritvika%20Nagula%2C%20a%20senior%20software%20engineer%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20said%20she%20learned%20the%20hard%20way%20how%20to%20get%20promoted.%20